Wen Meme Stock bail outs $BBY?

Bed Bath & Beyond $BBY files for bankruptcy, has begun a liquidation sale, plans to close stores and lay off thousands of employees. Bed Bath & Beyond filed for bankruptcy because of declining sales and competition from online retailers. In the early 2000s, the rise of online retailers like Amazon began to deteriorate the company's sales, as shoppers were able to find lower prices and a wider selection of products online. Bed Bath & Beyond was slow to adapt to the changing retail landscape. The company continued to rely on its brick-and-mortar stores, even as more and more shoppers were moving to online shopping.
